<headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 20 at 3:22PM AST  by NWS San Juan</headline>
<description>...Rainbands, with strong thunderstorms, will impact portions of
Saint John and Saint Thomas...
At 320 PM AST, a line of strong thunderstorm was approaching St John
from the east, moving west at 25 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts of 40 to 50 mph and heavy rain.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Heavy rain may cause temporary street flooding especially
in poor drainage areas.
Locations impacted include...
St John, Charlotte Amalie West, Charlotte Amalie East, Charlotte
Amalie, Anna`s Retreat and Cruz Bay.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.00 IN
MAX WIND GUST...50 MPH</description>
<instruction>Motorists should slow down and be prepared for possible loss of
control due to hydroplaning.</instruction>
